.TH POOL_TEST 8 "2025" "POOL Protocol" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
pool_test \- POOL protocol testing and benchmarking tool
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B pool_test
.I command
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B pool_test
provides testing and benchmarking capabilities for the POOL protocol.
It can verify connectivity, measure throughput, and stress-test the
kernel module.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B bench \fIpeer_ip\fR [\fIsize_mb\fR]
Run a throughput benchmark transferring the specified amount of data
(default: 100 MB) to the peer and measuring encrypted transfer speed.
.TP
.B ping \fIpeer_ip\fR [\fIcount\fR]
Send heartbeat packets and measure RTT. Defaults to 10 pings.
.TP
.B stress \fIpeer_ip\fR [\fIsessions\fR]
Open multiple simultaneous sessions and transfer data to stress-test
the module's concurrency handling.
.SH OUTPUT
Benchmark results include:
.RS
- Throughput in MB/s and Mbps
.br
- RTT (mean, min, max, jitter)
.br
- Packet loss rate (parts per million)
.br
- Rekey events during transfer
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR poolctl (8),
.BR poold (8)
